target_assessment.type_match_reasoning: The auditor failed to identify any vulnerabilities, including the target reentrancy issue.

notes: The auditor completely missed the cross-function reentrancy vulnerability. In function _0x0353ce, the contract performs an external call (line 43) before a final state check (line 45). An attacker can use the callback to call _0x1045d1 (exit market), which sets _0x771f54[msg.sender] to false. When the execution returns to _0x0353ce, the health check _0x2ff8d2(msg.sender, 0) will return true because line 33 returns false if the user is not in the market, effectively bypassing the collateral check while keeping the borrowed funds.
